\sum_{n=1}^{\infty}{\frac{1}{n^p}}\text{ converges} \Leftrightarrow \int_{1}^{\infty}{\frac{1}{x^p}} \text{ converges}
\int_{1}^{\infty}{\frac{1}{x^p}}=\lim_{t\to\infty}{\left(\frac{t^{1-p}}{1-p}-\frac{1}{1-p}\right)}=\left\{\begin{align}\infty, \quad &p\le1 \\\frac{1}{p-1}, \quad &p>1 \end{align}\right.
p\ge 1
p>1
